<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div xml:id="PN379-intro">
      <p type="edition">tiṇai, atu. tuṟai, pariciṟṟuṟai. ōymāṉ villiyātaṉaip puṟattiṇai naṉṉākaṉār.
      </p>
      <p xml:lang="en" type="translation">  
      </p>
    </div>
    <div xml:id="PN379">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>yāṉē peṟukavaṉ ṟāṇiḻal vāḻkkai</l>
<l>yavaṉē peṟukaveṉ ṉāvicai nuvaṟa</l>
<l>ṉellari toḻuvar kūrvāṇ maḻuṅkiṟ</l>
<l>piṉṉai maṟattō ṭariyak kalcet</l>
<l>taḷḷal yāmaik kūṉpuṟat turiñcu</l>
<l>nellamal puravi ṉilaṅkai kiḻavōṉ</l>
<l>villi yātaṉ kiṇaiyēm peruma</l>
<l>kuṟuntā ḷēṟṟaik koḻuṅka ṇavviḷar</l>
<l>naṟuney yurukki nāṭcō <supplied>ṟīyā</supplied></l>
<l>valla ṉentai pacitīrt talleṉak</l>
<l>koṉvaral vāḻkkainiṉ kiṇaivaṉ kūṟak</l>
<l>kēṭṭataṟ koṇṭum vēṭkai taṇṭātu</l>
<l>viṭṭōy talaiya kuṉṟam piṉpaṭa</l>
<l><gap quantity="7" unit="character" reason="lost"/>ra vantaṉeṉ yāṉē tāyi</l>
<l>ṟūvāk kuḻavi pōla vāṅkat</l>
<l>tiruvuṭait tirumaṉai yaitutōṉṟu kamaḻpukai</l>
<l>varumaḻai maṅkuliṉ maṟukuṭaṉ maṟaikkuṅ</l>
<l>kuṟumpa<supplied>ṭu kuṇṭakaḻ</supplied> nīṇmati lūrē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l corresp="1">  “I, let me get a living in the shade of his foot. </l>
<l corresp="2">He, let him get fame by the utterances of my tongue. </l>
<l corresp="7">O great man, we are the Kiṇai players of Villiyātaṉ, </l>
<l corresp="6">lord of Laṅkā, [its] fields dense with paddy, </l>
<l corresp="3">where, when [their] sharp sickles become blunt, the paddy-cutting workmen </l>
<l corresp="4">think of stones that are difficult [to find] for [their] earlier force </l>
<l corresp="5">and rub [them] against the humped backs of the tortoises in the mire, </l>
<l>melting in white fragrant ghee with fat-eyes</l>
<l>the short-legged male [and] giving the rice of the day (8f.) </l>
<l corresp="10">our father is able to remove hunger”, </l>
<l corresp="12ab">upon taking in what we heard </l>
<l corresp="11">when so told your Kiṇai player, with a living by coming early, </l>
<l corresp="12cd">	desire not cooling down, </l>
<l corresp="13">while hills with sky-touching peaks were left behind </l>
<l corresp="14">………………… I came </l>
<l corresp="15">to that place like a calf that has not eaten without a mother, </l>
<l corresp="18">to [your] village with tall fortifications [and] a murderous deep moat, a stronghold, </l>
<l corresp="16">where fragrant smoke appearing wonderfully from those auspicious houses that possess Śrī, </l>
<l corresp="17">hides all the streets like coming rain clouds. </l>
</lg>
    </div>
